rno and was burnt to ashes, “the incident was caused by overspeeding on the part of the driver,” he said. The incident affected the free flow of traffic in the axis before the rescue operation was completed by the state firefighters, Federal Road Safety Corps, the Nigeria Police, and Ogun State Traffic Compliance and Enforcement Corps (TRACE). Confirming the incident, TRACE Public Relations Officer, Babatunde Akinbiyi said the incident had been incident with the Divisional Police Station, Ogbere. He warned the drivers of articulated vehicles especially tanker drivers to avoid reckless driving. He said, “the drivers of articulated vehicles especially tanker drivers should avoid excessive speed, drunk driving and have adequate rest before embarking on any journey in view of its attendant consequence,” Vanguard News Nigeria No fewer than 12 people were on Saturday burnt beyond recognition while three others susstained serious injuries in a ghastly accident along the Sagamu-Ore-Benin Expressway. September 9, 2012 In "News" James Ogunnaike Pandemonium broke out in Ijebu Ode, Ijebu Ode Local Government Area of Ogun State as an angry mob on Saturday set ablaze a refinery truck whose driver recklessly crushed an okada rider to death around old Ibadan road in Ijebu Ode area of Ogun. Mr Babatunde Akinbiyi, the… July 18, 2020 In "Metro" Nigeria Police was established to protect lives and property. What happened, last week, however, ran contrary to this creed as four persons in police uniform, operating in a bullion van, allegedly pursued a truck owned by a cement company, following which the driver lost control and rammed into some buses,… September 23, 2012 In "Just Human"